1. Activate the Camera: The webcam captures live video of your hand movements.

2. Detect Hands: The system looks for your hand and tracks key points (fingertips).

3 .Measure Thumb and Index Finger Distance: The system checks how far apart your thumb and index finger are.

4. Control Volume:
If your fingers are close (thumb and index close together), it increases the volume.
If your fingers are far apart, it decreases the volume.
Display the Result: It shows the webcam feed with hand landmarks, so you can see the hand detection in action.

5. Stop: Pressing 'q' stops the system.
